PRIVACY POLICY – VIEWCALLER
Last Updated:
30.1.2025
Welcome to ViewCaller (“the App”). This Privacy Policy (“Policy”) is provided by Smart Media Internet Marketing LTD (“Smart Media,” “we,” “us,” or “our”) and explains how we collect, use, share, and protect information in connection with our websites, the ViewCaller mobile application, and any related services (collectively, the “Services”).
By downloading, accessing, or using the Services, you agree to the terms of this Policy and (if applicable) the ViewCaller Terms of Service. If you do not agree, please do not use the Services.
1. SCOPE & REGIONAL NOTICES
EU, EEA, UK, & Switzerland Residents:
If you reside or are located in these regions, please see the supplemental provisions in Section 10 below.
California Residents:
If you reside in California, USA, please see additional provisions in Section 11 (CCPA/CPRA) below.
Nigeria Residents:
If you reside in Nigeria, please see Section 12 for additional provisions applicable under Nigerian law.
For any questions about how this Policy applies to you or about your region’s coverage, please contact us at
privacy@tap.pm
.
2. INFORMATION WE COLLECT
We collect various types of information to provide and improve our Services:
2.1 Profile & Account Information
Registration Data:
When you create an account or register, we may collect your name, phone number, email address, username, profile photo, or similar details.
Verification:
We verify phone numbers by sending a confirmation code via SMS or by initiating an automated “missed call.”
2.2 Device & Technical Information
Device Identifiers & Technical Data:
We may collect your IP address, device IDs (e.g., IMEI, Android ID, Advertising ID), device model, operating system version, browser type, language settings, and time zone.
Usage Data:
This includes details such as pages/screens visited, taps, clicks, install dates, last usage dates, crash logs, performance data, and debug information.
2.3 Call Log Data
Purpose:
To provide caller identification, spam blocking, and related phone features.
Ephemeral Processing:
Call log data is processed in real time on your device (to display caller information such as name or spam status) and is immediately discarded. We do not store call logs on our servers.
Default Handler Permissions:
We request default call or SMS handler permissions only when essential to our core functionality.
2.4 Contacts (Address Book)
Usage:
With your explicit consent, the App may access your local device address book to display contact names for caller ID or to enhance spam detection.
Local Processing:
We do not upload or store your contacts on our servers; any matching is done locally on your device.
2.5 SMS and MMS Data
Purpose:
With your explicit consent, the App may access SMS and MMS data on your device to identify and block spam or assist with message organization.
Limited Scope:
We process only limited metadata (e.g., message IDs, timestamps, media types) on your device and do
not
store, transmit, or share the content of your messages.
2.6 SMS AND MMS DATA (SPECIAL NOTICE)
Processing Details:
Identify and Block Spam:
We process SMS and MMS data locally to detect and block unwanted spam messages.
Assist with Message Organization:
We help categorize or organize your messages within the App.
Local-Only Processing:
All SMS/MMS data processing occurs solely on your device. No message content is stored, transmitted, or shared with our servers.
Consent-Based:
This processing is performed only with your explicit consent, and you can revoke this permission via your device’s settings at any time.
2.7 Purchase Information
Subscription Data:
If you subscribe to premium features or an ad-free version, we collect payment confirmations or subscription status. Payment processing is handled by third-party platforms (e.g., Apple In-App Purchase, Google Play Billing); we do not store full payment credentials.
2.8 Online Activity & Cookies
Tracking Technologies:
We and our partners may use cookies, mobile SDKs, pixels, and similar technologies to collect information about your usage of the Services, measure engagement, and deliver relevant ads.
Further Details:
Please see Section 9 for our Cookie and Tracking Technologies information.
2.9 Other Information You Provide
Additional Data:
This includes information submitted via surveys, promotions, or customer support inquiries.
3. HOW WE USE YOUR INFORMATION
We use the information collected for various legitimate purposes, including:
Service Provision & Enhancement
Operating, maintaining, and personalizing our Services (e.g., caller ID, spam detection).
Analyzing usage trends to improve features, fix bugs, and optimize the user experience.
Communication
Responding to inquiries, support requests, and technical issues.
Sending important notifications regarding changes to our Services, policies, or terms.
Marketing & Advertising
With your consent, displaying relevant ads in the free version of the App.
Measuring ad campaign performance and sending promotional offers (you may opt out at any time).
Security & Fraud Prevention
Detecting, preventing, and investigating malicious, fraudulent, or unauthorized activity.
Enforcing our Terms of Service and protecting our users.
Legal & Compliance
Complying with applicable laws, regulations, legal processes, and government requests.
Cooperating with law enforcement or public authorities when necessary.
Aggregated Analytics
Creating de-identified, aggregated statistics and insights for research and reporting that cannot be used to identify you individually.
4. HOW WE SHARE YOUR INFORMATION
We do not sell or rent your personal information. However, we may share data in the following circumstances:
With Your Consent:
When you explicitly agree to share your information with specified third parties or request us to do so.
Service Providers & Partners:
We share information with trusted vendors (e.g., cloud hosting, analytics, payment processors, ad networks) who support our Services. These partners are contractually obligated to safeguard your data and use it only for the purposes we specify.
Advertising Partners:
In the free version of the App, we may share limited data (e.g., advertising identifiers, aggregated usage data) with ad networks to serve targeted ads. You may opt out via your device settings.
Legal & Safety Requirements:
When required by law, legal process, or government request, or to protect our rights, property, or the safety of our users or the public.
Business Transfers:
In the event of a merger, acquisition, financing, sale of assets, or bankruptcy, your information may be transferred under appropriate confidentiality measures.
5. DATA SECURITY & RETENTION
5.1 Security Measures
We implement industry-standard safeguards—including encryption, access controls, and secured networks—to protect your data against unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure.
While we strive to protect your information, no method of transmission or storage is 100% secure.
5.2 Data Retention
Call Log & SMS/MMS Data:
Processed locally on your device and not stored on our servers.
Other Data:
Retained only as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes described in this Policy, comply with legal obligations, or resolve disputes.
6. YOUR RIGHTS & CHOICES
Depending on your location, you may have certain rights regarding your personal data, including:
Access & Correction:
Request access to or correction of your personal data.
Deletion:
Ask us to delete your personal data in certain circumstances.
Objection or Restriction:
Object to or request restrictions on our processing of your data.
Data Portability:
Request a copy of your data in a portable format.
Consent Withdrawal:
Withdraw consent for specific data uses (e.g., call logs, contacts, SMS/MMS, marketing communications).
Managing Permissions:
You can enable or disable permissions for call logs, contacts, and SMS/MMS via your device’s settings.
For marketing and advertising, you can adjust your device’s “limit ad tracking” settings or opt out via available options.
To exercise any of these rights or for any privacy concerns, please contact us at
privacy@tap.pm
.
7. INTEREST-BASED ADVERTISING & OPT-OUT (FREE VERSION ONLY)
If you use the free version of the App, we may work with third-party advertising partners to display targeted ads. These partners may use cookies, device identifiers, and similar technologies to collect data about your usage across our Services and other platforms.
Opt-Out Options:
iOS:
Go to Settings > Privacy > Tracking and disable “Allow Apps to Request to Track” for ViewCaller, or disable tracking under Apple Advertising.
Android:
Go to Settings > Privacy > Ads and select “Reset advertising ID” or “Delete advertising ID” (consult Google’s guidelines for older Android versions).
YourAdChoices:
Visit
https://youradchoices.com
for additional opt-out options.
8. CHILDREN’S PRIVACY
Our Services are not intended for children under the age of 13 (or the applicable age of consent in your jurisdiction). We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe that we have inadvertently collected such data, please contact us immediately so we can remove it.
9. COOKIES & TRACKING TECHNOLOGIES
We and our third-party partners may use cookies, beacons, SDKs, pixels, and similar technologies to:
Remember your preferences.
Understand usage patterns and improve the performance of our Services.
Deliver relevant advertisements (in the free version).
You can typically control cookies through your browser or device settings; however, disabling cookies may affect some features of our Services.
10. ADDITIONAL PROVISIONS FOR EU/EEA, UK, & SWITZERLAND
For users located in the EU, EEA, UK, or Switzerland:
Legal Bases:
We process your personal data based on your consent, the performance of a contract, our legitimate interests (such as enhancing and securing the Services), or to comply with legal obligations.
Data Transfers:
If we transfer your data outside these regions, we use safeguards such as Standard Contractual Clauses to ensure your data remains protected.
11. CALIFORNIA PRIVACY RIGHTS (CCPA/CPRA)
For California residents:
Categories of Personal Data:
We collect personal information as described in Section 2.
Your Rights:
You have the right to request access to, deletion of, or correction of your personal data, and to opt out of the sharing of your personal information for targeted advertising. You will not be discriminated against for exercising these rights.
No Sale of Data:
We do not sell your personal information.
How to Request:
To submit a verifiable consumer request, please email us at
privacy@tap.pm
with “California Privacy Rights” in the subject line.
12. ADDITIONAL PROVISIONS FOR NIGERIA
For Nigeria residents:
We comply with applicable
Nigerian data protection laws
, including the Nigeria Data Protection Regulation (NDPR).
Your Rights:
You have the right to access, rectify, and request deletion of your personal data, and to withdraw consent for data processing where applicable.
For inquiries or requests regarding your data, please contact us at
privacy@tap.pm
.
13. CONTACT US
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, or if you wish to exercise your rights, please contact us at:
Smart Media Internet Marketing LTD
Attn: Legal – Privacy
Sderot Hayahasut 11
Beer Sheva, Israel
Email:
privacy@tap.pm
